  "prompt": "Do the prime minister of our country require visa to visit any country?",
  "response": "Whether the Prime Minister of your country requires a visa to visit another country depends on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Bilateral Agreements:** Some countries have agreements that allow certain dignitaries, including prime ministers, to enter without a visa.\n\n2. **Diplomatic Protocols:** Often, heads of government are granted visa-free entry or receive visas on arrival as a matter of diplomatic courtesy.\n\n3. **Specific Country Policies:** Some countries may have specific policies for high-ranking officials that differ from standard visa requirements.\n\nTo provide a more accurate answer, I would need to know which country your Prime Minister is from and which country they plan to visit. Generally, however, prime ministers often receive special treatment and may not need to go through the standard visa application process.",
